The paper discusses nature- and bio-inspired algorithms for optimization problems, which are commonly used in the field of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves a critical analysis of the behavior of these algorithms, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes recommendations for better methodological practices, which is relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
